  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through multiple transactions or financial systems. Specific legal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of funds through complex financial transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into the legitimate economy\n\nMost legal definitions require:\n- Knowingly concealing the origin of criminal proceeds\n- Attempting to disguise the true source of funds\n- Engaging in financial transactions to hide illegal income\n\nPenalties often include significant fines and potential imprisonment, depending on the jurisdiction and specific circumstances of the offense.\n\nWould you like me to provide more detailed information about money laundering laws in a specific country or context?",
